      <h1>
        Notes on handling audio assets for Digital Cinema
      </h1>
    </div>

    <div class="content wikistyle gollum textile">
      <p><a href="http://www.cinecert.com/asdcplib/">asdcplib</a> is a reference implementation of <span class="caps">SMPTE</span> and <span class="caps">MXF</span> Interop “Sound &amp; Picture Track File” formats. You can use it on the command line to stuff digital cinema assets into <span class="caps">MXF</span> “containers”, calculate message digests of these containers (needed in <span class="caps">CPL</span> and <span class="caps">PKL</span>), generate UUIDs, extract track essence etc.</p>
<ul>
	<li>
<strong>How to map discrete audio files</strong>: <span class="caps">DCI</span> allows for 5.1, 7.1 and up to 14 tracks + HI (hearing impaired listeners track) + VI (visually impaired listeners track). asdcplib’s main tool <strong>asdcp-test</strong> maps given audio files in the order they appear on the command line.</li>
</ul>
<p>In order to map discrete 5.1 files you would tell asdcp-test to</p>
<p><code>asdcp-test -c audio.mxf audio_left.wav audio_right.wav audio_center.wav audio_low_frequency_effect.wav audio_left_surround.wav audio_right_surround.wav</code></p>
<p>because <code>L - R - C - LFE - LS - LR</code> is the 6-channel mapping order specified in the <a href="http://www.dcimovies.com/specification/index.tt2"><span class="caps">DCI</span> specs</a> (See section <i>3.3.3 Channel Mapping</i> for 6-channel and 8-channel mappings).</p>
<p>Also see asdcplib’s <code>src/AS_DCP.h</code>:<br>
<code>CF_CFG_1, // 5.1 with optional HI/VI</code><br>
<code>CF_CFG_2, // 6.1 (5.1 + center surround) with optional HI/VI</code><br>
<code>CF_CFG_3, // 7.1 with optional HI/VI</code></p>
<ul>
	<li>
<strong>Notes for a ffmpeg/sox audio pipeline</strong>:
	<ul>
		<li>relevant ffmpeg options:
		<ul>
			<li>-acodec (see available formats with “ffmpeg -formats”, among those see pcm_s24daud/<span class="caps">PCM</span> D-Cinema audio signed 24-bit)</li>
			<li>-map (set stream mapping from input streams to output streams)</li>
			<li>-ar (set the audio sampling frequency)</li>
			<li>-ac (set the number of audio channels)</li>
			<li>-vn (disable video)</li>
			<li>-sn (disable subtitle)</li>
		</ul>
</li>
		<li>relevant sox options:
		<ul>
			<li>-t wavpcm (see Peter Forret’s <a href="http://code.google.com/p/opencinematools/issues/detail?id=29#c0">initial report</a> and <a href="http://code.google.com/p/opencinematools/issues/detail?id=29#c2">his findings</a>. Also see Peter’s <a href="http://code.google.com/p/dcptoolkit/">dcptoolkit project pages</a>)</li>
		</ul>
</li>
	</ul>
</li>
</ul>
    </div>

